Products.description: The 2019 Bowman Chrome X Box was initially released on StockX in October 2019 as an IPO (Initial Product Offering). Each sealed case contains 5 boxes, with each box containing one graded prospect or rookie Green X-Fractor parallel numbered to 31. Within each 5 box case you are guaranteed one of the top 20 rookies or prospects on the checklist (see photo). The set has 100 total players on the checklist, 35 rookies and 65 prospects. The checklist includes rookie cards for rising stars, Fernando Tatis Jr., Vladimir Guerrero Jr., Pete Alonso, and Eloy Jimenez.

Products.description: The 2020 Topps Chrome Ben Baller Baseball set brings baseball card collectors a collaborationn between world-famous jewler, artist, musician and actor, Ben Baller. Initially released through Topps.com. The cards feature the typical Topps chromium finish combined with the blinged-out look Ben Baller brings to his work. Ben Baller did the cards for this 200 card set. Each Topps Chrome Ben Baller Baseball Hobby Box comes with 4 cards per pack and 24 packs per box. The base set checklist includes rookie cards for rising stars Bo Bichette, Randy Arozarena, Luis Robert, Yordan Alvarez and many more!

Products.description: 2020 Panini Donruss Football carries on as one of Panini Football’s most popular sets that features a retail release. The 2020 Donruss Football checklist features 400 cards, which includes 50 rookies and 50 of the popular Rated Rookies. The 2020 Panini Donruss Football Fanatics Exclusive Blaster Box comes with 8 cards per pack and 11 packs per box, and on average includes 1 Fanatics Blaster Exclusive Donruss Threads Orange per box on average. The Donruss Football Rated Rookies checklist includes Joe Burrow, Tua Tagovailoa, Justin Herbert, Jerry Jeudy, Chase Young, D’Andre Swift, and several more.
